@hypebeastkicks: German publishing house @taschen has announced plans for a new book examining the footwear archive and legacy of @adidas. Titled ‘The adidas Archive: The Footwear Collection,’ the book tells the story of the sportswear giant through more than 357 different shoes, including never-before-seen prototypes and one-of-a-kind originals. It’s available now for pre-order at the TASCHEN web store and will see a release on March 22.⁠⠀
Photo: TASCHEN

#hypeflix: It’s been confirmed that the original cast members of @friends are coming together for a reunion special to help launch @hbomax. Head to the link in our bio for more info. The special is set to debut alongside all 236 episodes of the show when HBO Max launches in May.⁠
Photo: @markseliger

@hypebeastart: Living room goals courtesy of @kaws. ⁠
Photo: @skarstedtgallery

This week on #TheHYPEreport, @thecamp0ut and our editors discuss the death of rapper Pop Smoke, the adidas Yeezy QNTM Quantum sneaker, Supreme’s S/S 2020 lookbook, and Jeff Bezos’s $10 billion dollar pledge to fight climate change.⁠
-⁣⁠
Link in bio. Thank you for tuning in and don’t forget to subscribe to #TheHYPEreport on wherever you get your podcasts.

@hypebeastkicks: @travisscott x @nikesb dropping today via Travis Scott web store!⁠⠀
Photo: @rayscorruptedmind

@hypebeastmag: HYPEBEAST Magazine Issue 28: The Ignition Issue celebrates individuals who are doing more than just contributing to important social conversations and highlights the embodiment of sustainable living. Grab the first issue of the decade by visiting the link in our bio!

#hypeAF: @burgerking has released a new video ad campaign promoting the Whopper burger. While not the most appetizing way to depict its new Whopper option, it highlights "the beauty of no artificial preservatives". Expect the artificial preservative-free Whopper to hit 400 locations in the United States by the end of 2020.⁠
Video: Burger King

#hypebeasttech: According to reports, @apple’s rumored AirPods "Pro Lite" could arrive by mid-2020. It’s expected to come at a lower price point as it might not include its active noise-canceling technology or include the option to purchase AirPods without the charging case. Head to the link in our bio for more details.⁠
Photo: Eddie Lee/HYPEBEAST

#hypeAF: @mastermindjapan_official and @medicom_toy are back with another BE@RBRICK, this time dressed in a glossy “Black Chrome.” Coming in sizes 100%, 400% and 1000%, the figure  will be available for raffle at Medicom Toy’s website come February 29. ⁠
Photo: Medicom Toy

#hypelife: @drxromanelli and @thelncc have come together once more for a bean bag chair made from upcycled @adidas tracksuit jerseys. The piece is padded all-over for a comfortable, usable finish, and comes paired with a matching footstall. It’s available now on LN-CC’s website for $8,400 USD. ⁠⠀
Photo: LN-CC

#hypeAF: Take a look at this 'Dragon Ball Z' Collector’s Chess Set. It features 18 custom-sculpted full-color busts of heroes and villains from Akira Toriyama‘s iconic anime, and comes complete with a Shenron-themed game board and a set of rules for the game. It’s available now at @theopgames for a price of $60 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: Usaopoly

#hypelife: Québec City-based architecture firm @bourgeoislechasseurarchitectes has opened the doors to Cabin A, a triangular-shaped cabin overlooking the St. Lawrence River. Inspired by the International Code of Signals, Alfa signal informs the structure’s overall design, while references to naval architecture are found throughout. The triangulated roof references sails facing the wind whereas a wood terrace evokes the upper deck of a ship. Swipe to take a look around.⁠⠀
Photo: @maximebrouillet

#hypeAF: @czinger_vehicles unveils the 21C, an all-new hybrid hypercar that has been made using 3D printing technology. The California-based automaker equipped the 21C with 937 BHP from the 2.88-liter twin-turbo V8 redlining at 11,000 RPM, and two hybrid components providing a total of 1,250 BHP at the wheels. Further numbers include an acclaiming 0-60 MPH in 1.9 seconds with a top speed of 248MPH. Only 80 units are reportedly being built coming at $1.7m each.⁠⠀
Photo: Czinger

@hypebeastart: "Your brain is trying to understand what it is. It moves like a creature but looks like a kinetic sculpture in a gallery."⁠
Video: @zhestkov

On this week's #hypebeastnews: Pop Smoke dies at age 20, Supreme drops SS20 Lookbook, John Wick’s “Hitman” Mustang goes on sale, Jeff Bezos pledges $10 Billion towards climate change, and ‘The Matrix 4’ footage surfaces.

@hypebeastkicks: @puma has partnered with @firstmileimpact to create a sustainable sportswear collection. First Mile aims to strengthen micro-economies in Haiti, Honduras, and Taiwan by collecting plastic bottles to create sustainable jobs and reduce waste. The collection is made entirely from recycled yarns and serves PUMA’s initiative of being “Forever Better”. Shop the entire collection on the PUMA website now.⁠⠀
Photo: PUMA⁠

#hypeflix: Despite Parasite‘s immense success recently at the Oscars, it was by no means the first South Korean movie to gain such global interest. Back in 2016, the world was presented with the zombie horror film Train to Busan, which became an international sensation, leading to an animated prequel called Seoul Station. At the time, it was also announced that a sequel had been green-lit, but it now appears that the upcoming film — titled Peninsula — though set in the same world as the original movie, will not be a proper sequel but a follow-up instead. Hit the link in bio for more info on the film.⁠
Photo: Yeon Sang-ho

@hypebeastkicks: @jumpman23 has transformed the Air Jordan 5 Low "Fire Red" into a golf shoe. It features a mixture of crisp white leather uppers with bright red detailing/branded accents that you've grown to love from the OG, all sitting atop golf-ready outsoles. These are set to release on February 28 for $225.⁠⠀
Photo: Nike

@hypebeastsports: @kingjames and his company @uninterrupted are now being sued for $33 million USD for allegedly stealing the slogan “I Am More Than An Athlete.” The claim comes from a non-profit youth organization in Maryland called Game Plan, who claims that James and his company had infringed on its copyright over the slogan which it trademarked back in 2016. James had started using the similar phrase “More Than An Athlete” only since 2018, after Fox News host Laura Ingraham told the now Lakers player to “shut up and dribble.”⁠
Photo: Steve Dykes/Getty Images

@hypebeaststyle: @undercover_lab has teamed up with @_mars89 for a new capsule collection. Dubbed “The Droogs Against War,” the special range is comprised of 11 items that express a mix of apparel and accessories. Head to the link in our bio for more details. They’ll be available online and at UNDERCOVER locations in Japan on February 29.⁠⠀
Photo: UNDERCOVER

@hypebeaststyle: @chanelofficial has unveiled an elegant J12 X-Ray watch. It gets its name due to the transparent sapphire case, bracelet, and dial which reveals the inner-workings of the Caliber 3.1 movement. The piece also features small baguette diamond markers on the dial, 46 diamonds laid into the bezel, and a single stone placed at the center of the crown. It’s set to release in a limited number of 12 examples for $626,000 USD each.⁠⠀
Photo: Chanel

#hypeAF: @mcdonalds has crafted limited edition burger scented candles for its Quarter Pounder Fan Club. It includes scents of “100% Fresh Beef,” “Ketchup,” “Pickle,” “Cheese,” “Onion” and “Sesame Seed Bun,” which smell better when burned together “for maximum deliciousness.” It’s set for a staggered release over at Golden Arches Unlimited.⁠
Photo: Golden Arches Unlimited

@hypebeastmusic: @theweeknd has announced a forthcoming ‘After Hours’ tour that’s kicking off in North America this June and winding through Europe in October. Check out the full tour dates via the link in our bio. Tickets will be available for purchase starting February 28.⁠
Photo: Phillip Faraone/Getty Images

@hypebeastkicks: @bape_japan continues to celebrate the BAPE STA sneaker’s 20th anniversary with four glossy colorways. Look for ‘em to release at its stores and website on February 22.⁠
Photo: BAPE

@hypebeastart: @banksy reveals some initial sketches for the Barton Hill street artwork.⁠⠀
Photos: Banksy
